Setup and Experiment
Instructions for
Fixed Device: iPhone/iPad
Mobile Device: Android
Overview of Tasks:
1. Install and transmit beacons from the iOS app
2. Install the Android app on your mobile device
3. Perform the experiments as per the
instructions in the video attached towards the
end
iOS App Installation (1)
● Before you start make sure your phone is updated to
iOS 13.4.1 Software.
● Download Testflight from App Store.
● Open this Link in Testflight:
https://testflight.apple.com/join/LWw7Hz8x
Or equivalently scan the QR code on the top
● Tap Install and Open the app
iOS App Installation (2)
● Open the app installed.
● Make sure you grant access to the
permissions required
● Turn on your Bluetooth
● Tap “Transmit Beacons”
Set up Fixed Device (1)
● Tap “Save Phone Data”
Set up Fixed Device (2)
● Click the ‘Toggle to Beacon’ switch
● Scan QR code on receiver phone
when done collecting data
Set up Fixed Device (3)
● Download .apk file (download link,
alternately scan the QR code above)
● Tap “Install”
Android App Installation (1)
● Tap “Allow from this source” if you are
installing via the QR code, otherwise
continue ahead
Android App Installation (2)
● Tap “Install Anyway” and “Don’t
Send” in the subsequent window
Android App Installation (3)
● Continue to “Open” the app.
Android App Installation (4)
● Open the app you just installed on your
mobile device
● Ensure Bluetooth is turned on
● Tap “Scan For Beacons”
Set up mobile device (1)
a. Select ‘<Your iPhone model>’ (eg. iPhone 7
plus) device name in drop down.
b. Tap “Start Collecting RSSI” after making
the device selection
Please see video in the next slide for further
instructions
